<b>Subject:</b> Re: Is my Great Staff working?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/povar.cgi?read=76" TARGET=_self>Is my Great Staff working?</A> (Lemaitre)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Wow. That was funny. I was sitting here reading this post and thinking "Man, what a boob." Then I look at the name on it and it's you! The Clueless Wizard of Erudin! Your damage that you do in battle is based on at least two things, but I think there is a third factor, though I can't think of what it is. The damage score on the weapon is obviously one fact, but your STR also comes in to play. You have a cap on how much damage you can do per hit that is based on your strength. You may have reached that cap at 13/hit. I read this somewhere, so it's not just me saying it. I think, but may be wrong, that the third factor is magically enhanced damage.

<P>Anyone thinking I was harsh in the beginning of this response needs to know that Lemming here and I are friends in RL and that I'm just picking on him. Though, being a lanky Erudite, he is sort of pathetic.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
